this is the start of my tic tac toe project for The Odin Project.

the idea is that we make the logic for this game using modules and IIFEs. No global code. 

on the webpage, there will be inputs to name player1 and player2, and a start game button. Current players turn, who one, or if it's a tie will be displayed.

7/1: 
after weeks of bashing my head against a wall trying to understand modules and IIFEs, I finally got an explination that makes sense: a module is a const that uses an IIFE to make an object with specific frameworks and functions that can't be changed and aren't in global namespace. So a module can be made as -> (Const gameLogic = IIFE) where the module is gameLogic and the IIFE defines and returns all the functions that it would take to run the game. Then you use gameLogic.funciton to do different things. 

7/2:
I've got the game logic all coded, as well as display controller and player inputs. I understand the module pattern better now and how it's intended to keep differnt parts seperate. This project has been a long, arduous challenge that I'm really proud to finish. 